  "local_port": 42508,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "My Instagram account with 8.5k followers just got hacked into. I've spent the the last hour looking up ways to hack it and trying to get it back and nothing's working. How can I get it back?",
  "response": "I'm sorry to hear that your Instagram account has been hacked. Here are some steps you can take to try to recover it:\n\n1. **Try Logging In**: First, try logging into your account with your usual credentials. Sometimes hackers do not immediately change the password.\n\n2. **Reset Your Password**: If you can't log in, try resetting your password. Go to the Instagram login page, click \"Forgot password?\" and follow the instructions. You should receive a password reset link on your email or phone number associated with the account.\n\n3. **Check Your Email**: Look for any emails from Instagram about account changes. If the hacker changed your email address, you might find an email from Instagram which allows you to revert the change.\n\n4. **Use Account Recovery Options**:\n    - On the login page, click on \"Need more help?\" or \"Forgot password?\".\n    - Select the account type you believe was hacked.\n    - Follow the instructions to verify your identity. Instagram may ask you to submit a photo of yourself holding a handwritten code.\n\n5. **Report the Hacked Account**:\n    - Go to the Instagram Help Center ([help.instagram.com](https://help.instagram.com)).\n    - Choose the option to report a hacked account.\n    - Fill in the necessary information and follow the steps provided.\n\n6. **Contact Instagram Support**: If you're not able to recover the account using the above methods, you may need to contact Instagram support directly. This can sometimes be done through the Instagram app or the website.\n\n7. **Enable Two-Factor Authentication**: Once you regain access, enable two-factor authentication to enhance the security of your account. This will require a verification code (often sent to your phone) whenever you log in from a new device.\n\n8. **Check Linked Accounts**: If your Instagram is linked to other accounts like Facebook, make sure the email and passwords for those accounts haven't been compromised. Change those passwords if needed.\n\n9. **Secure Your Email Account**: Since the email associated with your Instagram account is crucial for recovery, ensure that your email account is secure. Change your email password and enable two-factor authentication there as well.\n\n10. **Scan for Malware**: Sometimes hacking incidents could involve malware on your devices. Run a full system antivirus scan to make sure your device is secure.\n\nRemember to use strong, unique passwords for all your accounts and to be cautious of phishing attempts.\n\nGood luck, and I hope you recover your account soon!",
